Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Feet MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Dislocation' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Talocrural joint' radio button is enabled
And 'Subtalar joint' radio button is enabled
And 'Tarsometatarsal (Lisfranc)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Tarsometatarsal (Lisfranc)' radio button
Then 'Myerson' radio button is enabled
And 'Nunley-Vertullo (Rupture of the Lisfranc ligament)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Myerson' radio button
Then 'Type A (total incongruity)' radio button is enabled
And 'Type B (partial incongruity)' radio button is enabled
And 'Type C (divergent)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type A (total incongruity)' radio button
Then 'Media' radio button is enabled
And 'Lateral' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type B (partial incongruity)' radio button
Then 'Medial displacement (B1)' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial lateral displacement (B2)' radio button is enabled
And 'Total lateral displacement (B2)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type C (divergent)' radio button
Then 'Partial (C1)' radio button is enabled
And 'Complete (C2)' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Nunley-Vertullo (Rupture of the Lisfranc ligament)' radio button
Then 'Grade I' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III' radio button is enabled
